    "content": "nullSalesforce B2B Commerce for Visualforce\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Salesforce B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Get Started with B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Manage Storefront Details and Metadata\n Set Up Product Data for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Help Buyers Discover Products on Your Storefront\n Price and Sell Products for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Support Buyer Accounts for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Provide a Smooth Path to Purchase for Storefront Buyers\n Customize the Storefront User Experience\n Strategize for Storefront Success\n Internationalize Your Storefront\n Boost Storefront Traffic with SEO\n Track Storefront Activity with Google Analytics 4\n Create a Portal to Your Storefront from an Experience Builder Site\n B2B Commerce Featured Products Lightning Component\n B2B Commerce Header Lightning Component\n B2B Commerce Reorder Lightning Component\n B2B Commerce Spotlight Product Lightning Component\n Override the Default CSS for a B2B Commerce Lightning Component\n Localize B2B Commerce Lightning Components\n Create Associations between Multiple Storefronts and Experience...\n Show a Storefront at the Root of Your Domain\n Deliver Storefront Performance and Security\n Market Templates for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Solution Resources for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nVISUALFORCE B2B COMMERCE\nB2B Commerce Spotlight Product Lightning Component\n\nThe B2B Commerce Spotlight Product component shows one of your storefront's spotlight products on an Experience Builder page.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\n\nSalesforce Compatibility\n\nSalesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience for Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions.\n\n\n\n\nB2B Commerce Compatibility\n\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Winter ’21 (version 4.13)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Spring ’20 (version 4.12)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Summer ’19 (version 4.11)\nNOTE Yes, this component shows only one spotlight product, which differs from the Spotlight Products Visualforce widget on your storefront, which can show multiple spotlight products. To show multiple spotlight products on the Experience Builder page, add multiple B2B Commerce Spotlight Product components, and select different a spotlight product for each component.\n\nThe component uses the following criteria for showing a spotlight product:\n\nThe current user must be entitled to view the spotlight product.\nThe spotlight product shown depends on the product you select in the component's properties.\nIf you delete the record for the spotlight product selected for this component, this component shows an error. If you add this component in a sandbox org and then you migrate to a production org, the component doesn't update automatically. In either case, delete the component from your Experience Builder page, add it again, and select a spotlight product that exists in the current org.\n\nTo add the component to a page in Experience Builder, scroll to the Custom Components section of the Components panel and drag B2B Commerce Spotlight Product onto the page.\n\nTIP The default component that the managed package installs is managed code, styled for the Capricorn Coffee demo theme, and not customizable. To customize the default component for your Experience Builder site, submit a Support & Services case to request access to the component source code.\nProperties\nPROPERTY\tDETAILS\nProduct Detail Button Label\tLink text that navigates to the Product Detail page on the storefront for the spotlight product.\nShow Image On\tThe side of the component where you want the spotlight product's image to display. This property applies only to desktop view.\nChoose the Spotlight Product to Show\tSelect which spotlight product from your storefront that you want to show on the Experience Builder page.\nShow Price\tWhether the current user's entitled price displays in the component.\nPrice Label\tText that prefixes a featured product's price, such as Price.\nHeading\tThe component's title on the Experience Builder page.\nCSS Override Examples\n\nThis CSS changes the Product Detail button colors and text.\n\n.b2b_btn_spotlight .slds-button{\n    color: orange;\n    background-color: brown;\n}\n\nThis CSS changes the font size of the spotlight product name.\n\n.b2b_btn_spotlight {\n    font-size: 5rem;\n}\nSEE ALSO\nShow Spotlight Products and Featured Products\nOverride the Default CSS for a B2B Commerce Lightning Component\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
